## Advanced Marp Layout Techniques for Technical Presentations

### Slide Dimensions and Responsive Design
```css
/* Standard 16:9 format (default) */
section {
  width: 1280px;
  height: 720px;
  padding: 40px;
}

/* Responsive typography for technical content */
section {
  font-size: clamp(16px, 2.5vw, 28px);
}
h1 { font-size: clamp(24px, 4vw, 48px); }
h2 { font-size: clamp(20px, 3vw, 36px); }
```

### Advanced Split Layouts for Technical Content
```markdown
<!-- Architecture diagrams with explanations -->
![bg left:33%](system-architecture.jpg)
# System Overview
The proposed architecture consists of three main components:
- **Video Tokenizer**: Compresses visual input
- **Dynamics Model**: Predicts next frame tokens  
- **Action Model**: Learns discrete action space

<!-- Results comparison -->
![bg right:40%](results-chart.png)
# Experimental Results
Our method achieves:
- 15% improvement in FVD score
- 2x faster inference time
- Better controllability metrics
```

### Multi-Column Layouts for Comparisons
```css
/* Three-column comparison for ablation studies */
section {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  gap: 1.5rem;
}

/* Two-column for method vs baseline */
.comparison-layout {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  gap: 2rem;
}
```

### Dashboard-Style Layout for Results
```css
section {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-areas:
    "title title title"
    "metric1 metric2 metric3"
    "chart chart table"
    "conclusion conclusion conclusion";
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
  grid-template-rows: 80px 120px 1fr 60px;
  gap: 1rem;
}
```

